ICS 156: Networking Lab 1.10 ARP 1/3 nWhen a network device wants to transmit a packet to another device it needs to know both the IP address and the physical address of the destination. nIP address to physical address mapping is maintained in the ARP cache.ï¿½ nThe ARP cache is constantly updated. nNetwork devices can identify local and remote addresses using the subnet mask.